description.narrative: National and subnational capacity to respond to health-related disaster risks strengthened, which contributes to Child Health, Child Health (Covid), Health And Emergencies, Maternal And Newborn Health, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020 improved and equitable coverage of quality health interventions for Newborns, Children, Adolescent girls and Women across the continuum of care at community and Primary Health Care (PHC) level

title.narrative: National and subnational capacity to respond to health-related disaster risks strengthened

description.narrative: UNICEF had supported various disease outbreaks including, Cholera, measles, and Yellow Fever, besides the COVID-19 pandemic. UNICEF health section's key support for COVID-19 included risk communication and community engagement (RCCE), logistic and PPE supplies, coordination, and continuation of essential health services. UNICEF procured and distributed PPE including 9,000 coveralls protection, 68,000 face shield, 30,000 disposable surgical gown, 40,000 goggles, 250,000 n95 masks, 100,000 surgical masks. UNICEF supported outbreaks of Cholera, measles, and Yellow Fever in various regions, which included the provision of health commodities (CTCs, vaccines), operational cost, and technical assistance in planning, coordination, and monitoring of preparedness and response | Status:Met | As-of Date:24/08/2020
